This paper is about unsupervised neural machine translation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach that involves weight sharing and generative adversarial networks, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of latent space, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of image captioning as an application of the proposed approach, which could make cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
